Sentencas: The structure, electrical conduction, thermal expansion and electrochemical properties of the La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3d +La2NiO4+d (LSCF-LNO) composite cathodes were investigated with regard to the volume fraction of the LNO composition.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ + La2NiO4+δ Composite Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: No chemical reaction product between the two constituent phases was found for the composite cathodes sintered at 1,400 degrees C for 10h within the sensitivity of the XRD.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ + La2NiO4+δ Composite Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Compared to the performance of the LSCF cathode, the LNO composition in the composite cathode plays a role in deteriorating both electrical conductivity and electrochemical properties, however, improving the thermal expansion properties.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ + La2NiO4+δ Composite Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The trade-off between electrical conducting and thermal expansion classifies the composite cathode containing 30 volume percent (vol.%) LNO as the optimum composition.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ + La2NiO4+δ Composite Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For characterizing cathode performance in a single cell, a slurry spin coating technique was employed to prepare a porous cathode layer as well as a YSZ/Ce0.8Sm0.2O3d (SDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ + La2NiO4+δ Composite Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The optimum conditions for fabricating the YSZ/SDC electrolyte were investigated.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ + La2NiO4+δ Composite Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The resulting single cell with 70vol.% LSCF-30vol.%LNO (LSCF-LNO30) cathode shows a power density of 497mW cm2 at 800 degrees C, which is lower than that of the cell with a LSCF cathode, but still within the limits acceptable for practical applications.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ + La2NiO4+δ Composite Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
